    transliteration: "ajñānena āvṛtaṁ jñānaṁ tena muhyanti jantavaḥ | svātmajñānena sarvaṁ ca jñātaṁ bhavati tattvataḥ ||",
    translation: "Knowledge is covered by ignorance; thereby living beings are deluded. When ignorance is destroyed by Self-knowledge, then everything is truly known.",
